Descriptor.0: SEPICA>The Solar Energetic Particle Ionic Charge Analyzer

Link_text.0: Release notes and other info available at

Link_title.0: the ACE Science Center  Level 2 Data website

TEXT.1: The Solar Energetic Particle Ionic Charge Analyzer

TEXT.2: is the sensor on ACE, which is used to determine the

TEXT.3: charge state distribution of energetic particle distributions.

TEXT.4: SEPICA is designed to measure the ionic charge state, Q,

TEXT.5: the kinetic energy, E, and the nuclear charge, Z, of energetic ions above 0.2 MeV/Nuc.

TEXT.6: This includes ions accelerated in solar flares as well as in

TEXT.7: interplanetary space during energetic storm particle (ESP)

TEXT.8: and co-rotating interaction region (CIR) events. For low mass numbers

TEXT.9: SEPICA also separates isotopes -- for example, 3He and 4He.

TEXT.10: For more information about the SEPICA instrument, visit the SEPICA Home Page

TEXT.12: The quality of ACE level 2 data is such that it is suitable for serious

TEXT.13: scientific study.  However, to avoid confusion and misunderstanding, it

TEXT.14: is recommended that users consult with the appropriate ACE team members

TEXT.15: before publishing work derived from the data. The ACE team has worked

TEXT.16: hard to ensure that the level 2 data are free from errors, but the team

TEXT.17: cannot accept responsibility for erroneous data, or for misunderstandings

TEXT.18: about how the data may be used. This is especially true if the appropriate

TEXT.19: ACE team members are not consulted before publication. At the very

TEXT.20: least, preprints should be forwarded to the ACE team before publication.
